properties.description: This dataset contains the whole-brain parcellation of the JuBrain Cytoarchitectonic Atlas (Amunts and Zilles, 2015) in the MNI Colin 27 as well as the MNI ICBM 152 2009c nonlinear asymmetric reference space. The parcellation is derived from the individual probability maps (PMs) of the cytoarchitectonic regions released in the JuBrain Atlas, that are further combined into a Maximum Probability Map (MPM). The MPM is calculated by considering for each voxel the probability of all cytoarchitectonic areas released in the atlas, and determining the most probable assignment (Eickhoff 2005). Note that methodological improvements and integration of new brain structures may lead to small deviations in earlier released datasets.

properties.name: ICBM 2009c Nonlinear Asymmetric
properties.description: An unbiased non-linear average of multiple subjects from the MNI152 database, which provides high-spatial resolution and signal-to-noise while not being biased towards a single brain (Fonov et al., 2011). This template space is widely used as a reference space in neuroimaging. HBP provides the JuBrain probabilistic cytoarchitectonic atlas (Amunts/Zilles, 2015) as well as a probabilistic atlas of large fibre bundles (Guevara, Mangin et al., 2017) in this space.
